<section class="sect" id="benchmarks">
  <div class="wrap">

    <p class="sect-eyebrow" data-reveal>Performance</p>
    <h2 class="sect-heading" data-reveal>Measured in millions<br />of operations per second.</h2>

    <div class="bench-table" data-stagger>
      <div class="bench-row bench-row--head">
        <span>Operation</span>
        <span>Throughput</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-row">
        <span class="bench-op">input.get() — cached</span>
        <span class="bench-val">34.6 M ops/s</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-row">
        <span class="bench-op">node.get() — cached</span>
        <span class="bench-val">44.3 M ops/s</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-row">
        <span class="bench-op">input.set() + node.get()</span>
        <span class="bench-val">1.9 M ops/s</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-row">
        <span class="bench-op">chain depth 10 — set + get</span>
        <span class="bench-val">503 K ops/s</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-row">
        <span class="bench-op">diamond (1 → 4 → 1) — set + get</span>
        <span class="bench-val">1.5 M ops/s</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-row">
        <span class="bench-op">100 independent chains — set 1, get 1</span>
        <span class="bench-val">3.7 M ops/s</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="bench-note" data-reveal>
      Versus a naive approach on 50 widgets with one width change:
      <strong>417 K vs 4.23 M ops/s — 10× faster.</strong>
    </p>

  </div>
</section>

